lingmo-window (1.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Architecture correction phase: refactored to pure SDK library.
    - Removed Windows-specific code (DWM, Mica, Acrylic).
    - Refactored WindowEffect -> WindowEffects: pure state holder, no platform impl.
    - Refactored Window from QWindow subclass -> WindowController: decoupled abstraction.
    - Added WindowChrome: CSD hit-testing, drag regions, resize margins.
    - Restructured src/platform/: Wayland, X11, Generic subdirectories.
    - Removed WindowEffectManager (contained Windows DWM code).
    - Removed WindowManager (over-engineered strategy pattern, now delegated to controller).
    - Added architecture constraint tests (no KWin, no KDE, no Windows API).
    - Updated QML module: WindowEffect -> WindowEffects.
    - All visual properties sourced from lingmo-theme.

 -- Lingmo OS Team <team@lingmo.org>  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 18:50:00 +0000
